01:43.195 --> 01:44.864
Mom?

01:45.282 --> 01:47.095
Dad?

01:47.199 --> 01:48.951
Al?

01:49.472 --> 01:51.222
Hello!

02:15.311 --> 02:16.998
Al?

02:32.933 --> 02:34.849
The thunderbolt.

03:30.678 --> 03:31.885
Papa.

03:34.244 --> 03:35.993
Papa.

04:01.323 --> 04:03.052
Papa.

04:58.683 --> 05:01.287
Okay! Bring her in!

05:10.402 --> 05:12.133
That's it.

05:13.301 --> 05:17.034
Okay, now put those... yeah.
Secure it over there.

05:17.868 --> 05:20.037
Yeah, the other tree.

05:20.141 --> 05:22.477
That's it. Tighten it up.

05:23.103 --> 05:25.813
Okay! Up, up!

05:26.294 --> 05:27.857
Go.

05:31.736 --> 05:34.093
Over! A little bit.

05:34.197 --> 05:37.075
Watch it. Back it up. Keep it going.

05:37.179 --> 05:39.660
Back her up. That's it.

06:02.237 --> 06:04.604
Hey, Terry,
what's that thing called again?

06:04.708 --> 06:07.334
A geode. Thunder eggs.

06:07.751 --> 06:12.445
- I don't think we should be doing this.
- Hey, chill out. They'll never know.

06:13.070 --> 06:14.946
My dad will have a seizure.

06:15.050 --> 06:18.138
It's your own fault. You should have
called me before they filled it in.

06:18.242 --> 06:20.723
- Yeah, but...
- There's gotta be more down there.

06:20.827 --> 06:24.725
You know how much you can get
for a big one? 100 bucks.

06:32.819 --> 06:35.529
It smells like something died in there.

06:35.634 --> 06:38.324
- It looks like a cave.
- Wicked.

06:38.428 --> 06:40.992
- Be careful.
- Here.

06:44.559 --> 06:47.602
- Jeez.
- It's nothin'.

06:52.755 --> 06:54.672
What is it?

06:56.489 --> 06:58.597
What the hell was that noise?

06:58.701 --> 07:01.032
I don't think we should be doing this.

07:04.412 --> 07:06.353
Who cares?

07:06.978 --> 07:08.916
We're rich.

07:13.400 --> 07:15.296
Come on.

07:16.967 --> 07:20.793
Al, don't! Wait a sec!
You promised I could have these.

07:20.898 --> 07:23.619
I said that 3 months ago.
They've been sitting in my room.

07:23.723 --> 07:25.267
But, Al...

07:25.371 --> 07:28.165
Quit calling me Al. My name is Alexandra.

07:28.270 --> 07:31.448
- Well, aren't we gonna launch 'em?
- You can do whatever you want.

07:31.552 --> 07:34.268
- I've gotta go.
- Where?

07:34.372 --> 07:37.988
- You promised we could launch them.
- I'm going shopping with Lori and Linda.

07:38.092 --> 07:40.260
The Lee sisters.

07:40.886 --> 07:43.264
Al, wait! What about the thunderbolt?

07:43.368 --> 07:46.601
Just forget about the thunderbolt.
It's gone.

07:47.540 --> 07:51.021
What do you need her for, anyway?
I mean, what's the big deal?

07:51.856 --> 07:54.400
Well, ever since I burnt
a hole on the roof,

07:54.504 --> 07:58.821
my dad says I can't launch any
of my rockets without supervision.

07:59.238 --> 08:01.480
Hey, I'll supervise.

08:01.584 --> 08:03.847
Hey! You guys, wait for me!

08:03.951 --> 08:05.889
Come on!

08:06.162 --> 08:08.141
Get in the car!

08:30.062 --> 08:33.044
- What are those for?
- Live cargo.

08:33.148 --> 08:36.807
Forget it. Got wet in the trash. Totaled.

08:37.537 --> 08:39.433
How long do you think
they can live without air?

08:39.539 --> 08:43.509
- Hey, man, that's cruel.
- Come on. It's neat.

08:49.894 --> 08:51.100
Glen?

08:53.542 --> 08:55.272
Glen!

09:06.306 --> 09:09.747
It's just irresponsibility. I don't know.

09:09.851 --> 09:12.248
Is it too late to call Mrs. Vandergrift?

09:12.353 --> 09:17.405
Daddy, please, you can't call a baby sitter.
I'm gonna be 16 in wot weeks.

09:17.509 --> 09:20.362
You said I was mature enough
to accept the responsibility.

09:20.466 --> 09:24.406
And, honestly, I promise
there won't be any problems.

09:24.511 --> 09:28.452
Well, what do you think, Glen?
Can you be trusted?

09:28.556 --> 09:29.892
I don't know.

09:29.996 --> 09:34.583
If your father and I agree to let the two
of you stay alone for 3 whole days,

09:34.688 --> 09:38.170
- how can we be sure that you'll behave?
- It was Terry that started it.

09:38.275 --> 09:41.237
If Terry jumped off a bridge,
I suppose you'd jump off, too.

09:41.341 --> 09:43.269
Sure. Why not?

09:43.373 --> 09:46.572
Look, I can take care of Terry
and I can take care of Glen.

09:46.677 --> 09:49.202
I can take care of this house.

09:49.306 --> 09:51.036
Please?

09:53.353 --> 09:57.419
All right. But, you, young man,
are grounded for the weekend.

09:57.523 --> 10:01.277
And that means that you do not leave
this house until we come back.

10:01.381 --> 10:04.342
Grounded? For real?

10:04.447 --> 10:06.344
For real.

10:06.761 --> 10:10.412
And after dinner, pal,
you fill in that hole.

10:11.527 --> 10:13.246
Okay.

10:24.258 --> 10:26.237
Good night, Glen.

10:28.241 --> 10:30.346
No, leave it on.

10:34.498 --> 10:36.179
Glen?

10:36.792 --> 10:39.128
What's with you today?

10:39.232 --> 10:43.277
It's... I don't know.
It's something about that hole.

10:43.798 --> 10:45.696
What do you mean?

10:46.322 --> 10:48.679
I don't know. It's just weird.

10:49.305 --> 10:52.953
Well, you... you filled it in, didn't you?

10:53.058 --> 10:55.675
Yeah. But Terry told me something.

10:55.998 --> 10:58.835
- What?
- Well, he said a long time ago,

10:58.940 --> 11:02.338
when they were building our house,
a workman got killed.

11:02.442 --> 11:04.925
And the other workmen
didn't want to tell the police,

11:05.029 --> 11:07.762
so they sealed him up in one of our walls.

11:08.907 --> 11:10.893
Look, son...

11:11.774 --> 11:14.132
let me tell you something about Terry.

11:14.862 --> 11:17.020
You remember last year
when Terry's mom died.

11:17.124 --> 11:18.939
Yeah.

11:19.043 --> 11:22.347
Well, ever since then,
Terry's been a little strange.

11:24.089 --> 11:27.718
I think he's kind of angry inside
that his mom's gone.

11:28.657 --> 11:33.099
So, you just remember that
when he gets destructive or...

11:33.203 --> 11:35.016
tries to scare you.

11:35.121 --> 11:38.374
I think he's just
a little confused, that's all.

11:39.469 --> 11:42.929
- You know what I'm saying?
- I think so.

11:44.150 --> 11:47.863
- You want me to turn the light on?
- No, it's okay.

11:47.968 --> 11:49.861
Good night, tiger.

11:51.157 --> 11:53.315
- Dad?
- Yeah.

11:55.475 --> 11:57.310
Never mind.

11:57.415 --> 12:00.634
- Good night.
- Good night, pal.

12:56.744 --> 12:59.206
Don't forget that Angus
gets his pills every day.

12:59.310 --> 13:01.895
Make sure they're hidden in his
dog food or he'll spit them out.

13:01.999 --> 13:05.003
- And I don't want him on the furniture.
- I know, Mom.

13:05.107 --> 13:07.712
- Goodbye, hon.
- Bye.

13:08.339 --> 13:11.259
- Bye, Mom.
- Goodbye.

13:11.364 --> 13:13.365
- Bye, Dad.
- See you guys.

13:13.469 --> 13:14.846
- Goodbye!
- Bye!

13:14.951 --> 13:15.805
Bye, Mom.

13:15.909 --> 13:19.369
And don't forget, the numbers
where we'll be are on the refrigerator.

13:19.473 --> 13:23.146
Al, if you need us for any reason,
don't be afraid to give us a call.

13:23.251 --> 13:26.128
- It's just being responsible.
- I know, Mom.

13:26.233 --> 13:28.939
- Remember, you stay in this weekend.
- Okay.

13:29.043 --> 13:32.072
And I want the house clean
when we come home. No parties.

13:32.176 --> 13:34.024
Okay!

13:34.970 --> 13:36.743
Lori! Linda!

13:36.847 --> 13:39.847
Hey, wow! Great party!

13:45.188 --> 13:47.356
I don't know. Here.

13:49.694 --> 13:52.967
What a tool. He just totaled his car.

13:53.071 --> 13:54.323
Brutal!

13:56.492 --> 13:58.973
Hey, somebody get this dog a beer.

14:04.478 --> 14:06.815
Put me down!

14:07.774 --> 14:09.899
Get away!

14:23.749 --> 14:25.707
Come on!

15:04.977 --> 15:08.648
Hey! Bug off, Angus! You stink!

15:08.752 --> 15:11.128
I'd like smell you when you're 97.

15:11.232 --> 15:13.131
He's not 97.

15:13.236 --> 15:15.246
In dog years.

15:21.598 --> 15:22.974
It's just not gonna break.

15:23.079 --> 15:25.236
Why don't we get
the Lee sisters to look at it?

15:25.340 --> 15:27.018
Yeah.

15:28.959 --> 15:33.408
No, we could throw it off the roof
tomorrow. Come on. Let's go party.

15:33.512 --> 15:37.279
- She won't let us.
- Sure she will. Why not?

15:37.384 --> 15:40.073
It's just... forget it.

15:57.633 --> 16:00.755
Told ya. Look at it.

16:03.995 --> 16:06.328
Is it supposed to do that?

16:07.540 --> 16:08.957
I don't know.

16:09.061 --> 16:12.900
Maybe it just got compressed air
when it was being formed or something.

16:19.072 --> 16:21.950
Look. It made some kind of marks.

16:22.054 --> 16:24.455
It's words. What's it say?

16:24.559 --> 16:26.309
It's weird.

16:26.413 --> 16:28.310
"Aca...

16:28.414 --> 16:29.960
"Kuto...

16:30.751 --> 16:32.460
"Alla...

16:32.564 --> 16:34.418
Eta."

17:00.821 --> 17:03.574
He made his way down the dark hallway.

17:03.678 --> 17:05.473
And the squeak keeps getting louder.

17:05.765 --> 17:08.537
And there's also this... like a laugh.

17:11.625 --> 17:14.190
And there's this weird tearing sound.

17:15.127 --> 17:18.710
So she goes to the door
and she opens it really slowly.

17:20.925 --> 17:24.450
And there, in the rocking chair,

17:24.554 --> 17:28.202
is the decomposed corpse
of her dead father.

17:30.185 --> 17:34.899
And in his lap is the severed head
of her boyfriend.

17:35.003 --> 17:38.785
And he's tearing out hair by the handful.

17:40.216 --> 17:42.738
- You made that up.
- I believe it.

17:42.842 --> 17:45.596
- Come on. It's bullshit.
- Weird things happen all the time.

17:45.700 --> 17:50.767
So we make up ghost stories to explain the
powers inside us that we don't understand.

17:51.393 --> 17:55.132
- What kind of powers?
- Well, like...

17:55.772 --> 17:58.985
- Will you guys ever do levitation?
- I've seen that. It's an illusion.

17:59.089 --> 18:03.618
No, it's a matter of concentration.
It really works.

18:04.782 --> 18:07.243
Do you believe in all that stuff?

18:10.393 --> 18:12.290
Me, too.

18:17.169 --> 18:21.046
Now, everyone just... clear your mind.

18:27.471 --> 18:30.683
- You broke your concentration.
- No, I broke my fingernail.

18:30.787 --> 18:34.416
- Too much junk food.
- It doesn't matter. It's not the weight.

18:34.520 --> 18:36.856
Hey, little man, come here.

18:37.273 --> 18:41.901
- Glen, go back to your room.
- No, come here. He'll be all right.

18:45.969 --> 18:49.493
- Let's see if we can levitate him.
- It's a cinch. He's a midget.

18:49.598 --> 18:51.979
- Okay, we'll just use two people.
- Sit down.

18:52.084 --> 18:53.831
Brad.

18:53.935 --> 18:58.398
Okay, hold your arms out, one on top
of the other, and make little circles

18:58.502 --> 19:02.214
to trans... transmit
and stimulate the energy.

19:02.527 --> 19:05.300
And everyone else concentrate.

19:07.657 --> 19:12.266
Now everyone just... clear your minds...

19:13.100 --> 19:16.062
and think of Glen as light as a feather.

19:16.166 --> 19:19.331
Concentrate.

19:19.920 --> 19:21.631
Okay.

19:21.839 --> 19:23.569
Like...

19:23.673 --> 19:25.030
dust...

19:25.134 --> 19:28.532
drifting in front of the windows, like...

19:29.054 --> 19:32.765
dandelions in the breeze.

19:33.329 --> 19:35.725
Rise.

19:36.853 --> 19:38.999
Rise...

19:40.065 --> 19:42.441
Hey. Help!

19:42.545 --> 19:44.963
Come on! Get me down!

19:53.203 --> 19:55.224
Are you okay?

19:58.666 --> 20:00.335
Glen.

20:02.546 --> 20:05.693
Maybe I won't do that... again.

20:07.134 --> 20:08.697
Glen.

20:08.801 --> 20:11.198
Glen, you all right?

20:13.505 --> 20:16.515
I think it's because he cried
in front of everybody.

20:18.395 --> 20:23.337
Hey, Glen... don't be embarrassed.
Crying's nothing.

20:23.963 --> 20:27.843
Remember when Trevor Stubblefield
pantsed me in front of the whole auditorium?

20:27.947 --> 20:32.657
Yeah. And I barfed on Steve Slavit
after the 12-minute run.

20:37.268 --> 20:40.739
- I want to call Mom and Dad.
- Glen, no.

20:40.843 --> 20:43.524
- I want you to call them.
- What am I gonna tell them?

20:43.628 --> 20:46.632
We're scared because we levitated Glen
and he broke the light? Great.

20:46.737 --> 20:49.374
- You must love Mrs. Vandergrift.
- Al...

20:49.478 --> 20:52.001
Look, Terry can sleep over
and keep you company.

20:52.158 --> 20:55.940
Let's all just get some sleep.
I'm gonna lock up.

20:59.435 --> 21:02.062
You really barfed on Steve Slavit?

21:02.167 --> 21:03.938
Yep.

22:51.468 --> 22:54.111
Terry...

22:54.677 --> 22:57.889
I love you.

22:59.453 --> 23:01.201
Mom?

23:03.810 --> 23:06.688
I need you.

23:06.792 --> 23:08.541
Mommy.

23:10.025 --> 23:13.966
I love you.

23:14.071 --> 23:16.595
Terry...

23:16.803 --> 23:18.552
come to me.

23:25.665 --> 23:27.211
Terry...

23:27.315 --> 23:30.272
I've missed you so much.

23:39.846 --> 23:43.036
No. Oh, no.

23:47.896 --> 23:49.875
Oh, no.

23:58.130 --> 24:00.240
The workman.

24:24.579 --> 24:26.498
Angus.

24:27.958 --> 24:29.916
What's going on?

24:59.322 --> 25:01.282
I'm really sorry.

25:01.803 --> 25:04.265
Yeah. He was really old.

25:04.369 --> 25:05.807
Yeah.

25:05.912 --> 25:09.393
He was 97.
They don't live much beyond that.

25:13.386 --> 25:17.002
Well... you want to come over later
and mess around?

25:17.106 --> 25:19.675
Sure. Yeah.

25:20.614 --> 25:22.762
Guess I'll see you later?

25:23.179 --> 25:25.304
See you later.

25:29.018 --> 25:30.701
Dad!

25:41.292 --> 25:43.406
Oh, great.

26:05.784 --> 26:07.702
What'd you do with Angus?

26:07.807 --> 26:11.210
Hey. Don't worry about it.

26:13.938 --> 26:16.294
Aren't you gonna call Mom and Dad?

26:16.399 --> 26:20.758
- No, I'll take care of it.
- Well, if you're not going to, I am.

26:20.863 --> 26:23.355
Glen, Mom and Dad
are gonna be home tomorrow.

26:23.459 --> 26:26.419
I don't care. I want them
to know what happened.

26:27.682 --> 26:29.826
You're not calling them.

26:44.927 --> 26:47.326
- Nice try.
- Fine.

26:47.431 --> 26:50.224
- I'll just call them later.
- What's the matter with him?

26:50.328 --> 26:53.458
- Isn't romper room on today?
- Buzz off, clown face.

26:53.563 --> 26:55.730
Don't you have to go upstairs
and change your pampers or something?

26:55.834 --> 26:59.780
- Don't you have to go and join the circus?
- Hey, you guys, come on.

27:24.718 --> 27:27.385
<i>In a time before the Earth,</i>

27:27.490 --> 27:31.349
<i>before the sun,
and before the light of the stars,</i>

27:31.453 --> 27:34.916
<i>when all was darkness and chaos,</i>

27:35.020 --> 27:38.911
<i>the old gods, the forgotten gods,</i>

27:39.016 --> 27:41.652
<i>ruled the darkness.</i>

27:41.964 --> 27:47.448
<i>But what was theirs now belongs
to the world of light and substance,</i>

27:47.552 --> 27:52.431
<i>and the old gods,
the rightful masters, are jealous,</i>

27:52.535 --> 27:57.041
<i>watching mankind with a hatred
that is as boundless as the stars,</i>

27:57.145 --> 28:01.899
<i>with plans for the destruction of man
that are beyond imagining!</i>

28:06.739 --> 28:12.411
<i>There's a passageway between
our physical world of light, pleasure,</i>

28:12.515 --> 28:16.728
<i>and their spiritual world
of madness and pain.</i>

28:16.833 --> 28:20.502
<i>A gate behind which the demons wait</i>

28:20.606 --> 28:25.152
<i>for the chance
to take back what is theirs!</i>

29:02.503 --> 29:06.299
Eric really likes you.
You've gotta come to the beach with us.

29:06.403 --> 29:08.696
- Well...
- Look, everybody's going.

29:08.800 --> 29:11.424
We're having a bonfire and everything.

29:11.528 --> 29:15.016
I don't know. I mean, I just can't go.

29:15.120 --> 29:18.123
Lookit, just leave him
some Gerber's. He'll be fine.

29:18.227 --> 29:20.959
Al, you can't go out. What about Angus?

29:21.064 --> 29:24.524
What about what happened last night?
You have to call Mom and Dad.

29:24.629 --> 29:27.819
- Glen, cool out.
- What's he talking about?

29:27.924 --> 29:29.392
Tell 'em.

29:31.990 --> 29:34.305
Angus died last night.

29:35.243 --> 29:38.643
- Tell 'em about the other stuff.
- There is no other stuff.

29:38.747 --> 29:43.172
What's the matter with you guys?
Something really scary happened last night.

29:43.700 --> 29:46.265
- What?
- The levitation.

29:46.369 --> 29:48.632
You guys were there.

29:48.736 --> 29:51.365
Hey, little man,
that was just an illusion.

29:51.469 --> 29:53.303
What do you know, lover boy?

29:53.407 --> 29:56.588
- What is your problem?
- You, Alexandra.

29:56.692 --> 30:00.142
- You're acting like a baby.
- Just shut up.

30:00.707 --> 30:03.938
- Fag.
- Hey.

30:05.440 --> 30:07.088
Tres uncool.

30:07.192 --> 30:09.590
- What are we waiting for?
- Look...

30:09.694 --> 30:12.281
You can't back down now. You have to go.

30:12.386 --> 30:15.721
I have to do something about Angus.
Take him to the animal shelter or something.

30:15.826 --> 30:18.140
- Eric will do it.
- Yeah. Yeah, I'll do it.

30:18.245 --> 30:21.832
And we'll all go to the mall and get munchies
and stuff and we'll all meet up there.

30:21.936 --> 30:24.110
Come on!

30:26.899 --> 30:29.900
- Don't be too long, Eric!
- Yeah, okay.

30:34.721 --> 30:36.972
- See ya.
- See you at the mall!

30:37.076 --> 30:40.306
Come on, Alexandra. He'll be okay.

32:54.944 --> 32:56.902
Oh, no.

33:21.720 --> 33:24.097
We're in big trouble.

33:24.201 --> 33:26.308
Tell me about it.

33:27.142 --> 33:31.272
- How could it come back by itself?
- I think I know what this means.

33:31.376 --> 33:34.941
You know, with the levitation
and all that other weird stuff?

33:35.671 --> 33:37.403
What?

33:38.133 --> 33:40.257
You got demons.

33:42.178 --> 33:44.869
- Demons?
- Come on.

33:44.973 --> 33:49.123
We better try to cover it up first.
You take this side here.

33:50.896 --> 33:52.794
I don't think this is gonna be enough.

33:52.898 --> 33:56.089
Give me a break. Come on.

33:57.444 --> 33:59.402
Slow down.

34:00.572 --> 34:03.010
How do you know so much about this stuff?

34:05.869 --> 34:08.056
I got something to show you.

34:12.042 --> 34:15.214
Shit! Closed. Sorry, dude.

34:15.690 --> 34:17.978
No vacancies.

34:20.967 --> 34:23.282
They're called sacrifyx,
and my dad brought it from Europe,

34:23.387 --> 34:25.326
and it's got all this stuff in it.

34:25.429 --> 34:28.621
See, these guys are, like,
really serious about demonology.

34:28.725 --> 34:31.038
And it's like they're trying to warn you.

34:32.687 --> 34:36.274
See? These guys knew.
They wrote their own music.

34:36.378 --> 34:39.833
They got their lyrics from this thing
called The Dark Book.

34:39.938 --> 34:41.989
That's like the Bible for demons.

34:42.802 --> 34:46.054
And here's the creepy part.
This is their only album.

34:46.159 --> 34:49.516
And after they made it,
they all died in a plane crash.

34:49.621 --> 34:53.041
- And look at this. Demon Lord.
- Terry, come on.

34:53.146 --> 34:58.401
Wait a minute. See? The lyrics in the album
tell you how to summon the demons.

34:58.505 --> 35:01.654
And there's this certain time
when these constellations are aligned

35:01.758 --> 35:04.472
when you can open the gate
and let the old gods...

35:04.576 --> 35:06.762
those are the demons, come through.

